article.headline: No. 23 Florida 75, Coppin St. 34
article.story:
GAINESVILLE, Fla. -- Lonnika Thompson scored 13 points, Marshae Dotson added 10 and No. 23 Florida beat Coppin State 75-34 Wednesday night.

The Gators (9-1), ranked for the first time in nearly three years, won their ninth consecutive game and kept the Eagles (0-8) winless this season.

Florida took over shortly after the opening tip, using a 20-2 run to turn a two-point game into a 44-17 rout at halftime. The Gators shot 53 percent from the field, forced 25 turnovers and finished 10-of-19 from 3-point range.

Jennifer Martin and Danielle Anders led Coppin State with six points apiece.

The Eagles cut into the big deficit with an 8-0 run in the second half. But Florida put the game away with an 11-0 spurt highlighted by three 3-pointers, one from Sharielle Smith and two from Thompson.

Florida's last game as a ranked team was Feb. 27, 2006.
